Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_inst_space_group(25.10)                  create_inst_space_group(25.10)

Name
       create_inst_space_group - Creates space group for instances with a spe-
       cific vertical or horizontal-distance constraint

Syntax
       create_inst_space_group

       [-help]

       <groupName>

       -inst <listOfInstances>

       {[{[  -spacing_y  <Distance>]  [-spacing_x  <Distance>]} [-checking_box
       {all|cross_only}]] | [-spacing_radial <Distance>]}

       Creates space group for instances with a specific vertical or  horizon-
       tal-distance constraint.

       The create_inst_space_group information can be saved in DB.

Parameters
       -checking_box {all cross_only}
              Checks  all  area  or  the intersection area from -spacing_x and
              -spacing_y.

              * cross_only: Checks the intersection  area  of  -spacing_x  and
                -spacing_y.  If  any  instance  violates  both  -spacing_x and
                -spacing_y, it is marked as a violation.

              * all: Checks all area covered by spacing_x  and  spacing_y.  If
                any  instance  violates -spacing_x or -spacing_y, it is marked
                as a violation. The constrained box is  ended  by  core/block-
                age/power domain/hard macro/row boundary.

              Default: cross_only

       <groupName>
              Specifies the name of the group.

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each create_inst_space_group parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man create_inst_space_group.

       -inst <listOfInstances>
              Specifies all instances that belong to the same space  group  by
              name.

       -spacing_radial <Distance>
              Specifies the radial distance, in microns.

       -spacing_x <Distance>
              Specifies  the  distance,  in microns, between each specific in-
              stance in the X direction. If you specify -spacing_x  only,  the
              tool  checks  the  left/right edges of each specific instance in
              the instance group across the y-axis in the db.

       -spacing_y <Distance>
              Specifies the distance, in microns, between  each  specific  in-
              stance  in  the Y direction. If you specify -spacing_y only, the
              tool checks the top/bottom edges of each  specific  instance  in
              the instance group across the x-axis in db traversing the row.

Related Information
